dlcUnitHwRev.name: dlcUnitHwRev
dlcUnitHwRev.description: The ASCII code of the hardware revision number.

dlcUnitHwOptions.name: dlcUnitHwOptions
dlcUnitHwOptions.description: A bit map, reported as the sum of all the values that correspond to installed options: realTimeClock ( 1) netPortT1 ( 2) netPortE1 ( 4) auxPortT1 ( 8) auxPortE1 ( 16) otherNetT1 ( 32) otherNetE1 ( 64) reserved1 (128) reserved2 (256) reserved3 (512) `netPortT1' and `netPortE1' are mutually exclusive and one of the two will always be TRUE. `auxPortT1' and `auxPortE1' are mutually exclusive; if both are FALSE, there is no AUX port present. `otherNetT1' and `otherNetE1' are mutually exclusive; if both are FALSE, there is no CSU port present.

dlcUnitSwRev.name: dlcUnitSwRev
dlcUnitSwRev.description: The ASCII code of the software revision number.

dlcUnitDataPorts.name: dlcUnitDataPorts
dlcUnitDataPorts.description: The number of data ports installed on the unit.

dlcUnitRam.name: dlcUnitRam
dlcUnitRam.description: The amount of usable ram in the unit, in KBytes.

dlcUnitRom.name: dlcUnitRom
dlcUnitRom.description: The amount of usable rom in the unit, in KBytes.

dlcUnitFlash.name: dlcUnitFlash
dlcUnitFlash.description: The amount of FLASH ROM in the unit, in KBytes. If dlcUnitFlash is 0, the Downloadable Code option is not installed.

dlcUnitSlotNum.name: dlcUnitSlotNum
dlcUnitSlotNum.description: The slot number the unit is in. If it's a stand alone unit, this object will return 0.

dlcUnitMibRev.name: dlcUnitMibRev
dlcUnitMibRev.description: The ASCII code of the MIB revision number.

dlcUnitFeatures.name: dlcUnitFeatures
dlcUnitFeatures.description: Feature configuration for Solo Select. The value returned is a bit mask of which feature key is on/capable when the corresponding bit is 1.

dlcUnitId.name: dlcUnitId
dlcUnitId.description: A name that uniquely and globally identifies the unit. The Unit ID must consist of (upper-case) letters 'A'..'Z' and digits '0'..'9'. The first character of the Unit ID may not be a digit.

dlcUnitProtectMode.name: dlcUnitProtectMode
dlcUnitProtectMode.description: When true, the unit configuration can not be changed from the front panel nor can tests be initiated or terminated from the front panel.

dlcUnitYellowEnable.name: dlcUnitYellowEnable
dlcUnitYellowEnable.description: When false, yellow alarm conditions are ignored when received from a Dsx1 port, and the unit will never transmit a Yellow Alarm signal on a Dsx1 port. This applies to all ports: mainNet, aux, otherNet.

dlcUnitNetPassFdl.name: dlcUnitNetPassFdl
dlcUnitNetPassFdl.description: Indicates which Dsx1 DTE port's FDL is connected to the `mainNet' FDL when this unit has no traffic of its own. Meaninigful values are `aux', `otherNet', and `noPort'.

dlcUnitMainClockSource.name: dlcUnitMainClockSource
dlcUnitMainClockSource.description: This is the primary transmit timing source.

dlcUnitAltClockSource.name: dlcUnitAltClockSource
dlcUnitAltClockSource.description: This is the alternate transmit timing source. It is used when the primary source is not available.

dlcUnitExtClockRate.name: dlcUnitExtClockRate
dlcUnitExtClockRate.description: The signal arriving at the BNC connector on the back of the unit, in units of KHz. Must be a multiple of 56 or 64 KHz (n*56 or n*64) or 1544. For T1 units, the largest acceptable value is 1544. For E1 units, the value can go up to 2048. For Solo CSU products, the value is fixed at 1544 and cannot be changed.

dlcUnitFullBandwidthLoopCode.name: dlcUnitFullBandwidthLoopCode
dlcUnitFullBandwidthLoopCode.description: Determines the loop codes we transmit for the Full Bandwidth Loop Up Remote and Loop Down Remote tests and the code we respond to when it's received on the NET port. For the fullBandwidthLoopCode, `v54' is an invalid value.

dlcUnitFractionalLoopCode.name: dlcUnitFractionalLoopCode
dlcUnitFractionalLoopCode.description: Determines the loop codes we transmit for the Fractional Loop Up Remote and Loop Down Remote tests and the code we respond to when it's received on fractional bandwidth.

dlcUnitTestLength.name: dlcUnitTestLength
dlcUnitTestLength.description: Determines the time interval after which tests are automatically terminated. Valid values are 0, 1, 15 and 60. 0 stands for unlimited, 1 for 1 minute, 15 for 15 minutes and 60 for 60 minutes.

dlcUnitUserPattern1.name: dlcUnitUserPattern1
dlcUnitUserPattern1.description: This is a sequence of the characters '0' and '1' that represents the first of two user patterns. The first character represents the first bit in the sequence.

dlcUnitUserPattern2.name: dlcUnitUserPattern2
dlcUnitUserPattern2.description: This is a sequence of the characters '0' and '1' that represents the second of two user patterns. The first character represents the first bit in the sequence.

dlcUnitBlockAllAlarms.name: dlcUnitBlockAllAlarms
dlcUnitBlockAllAlarms.description: When dlcUnitBlockAllAlarms is TRUE, the unit will never send any traps.

dlcUnitDsx1TrapEnableTable.name: dlcUnitDsx1TrapEnableTable
dlcUnitDsx1TrapEnableTable.description: A list of traps that are related to a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1TrapEnableEntry.name: dlcDsx1TrapEnableEntry
dlcDsx1TrapEnableEntry.description: An entry in the Dsx1 Trap Enable table.

dlcDsx1TrapPortId.name: dlcDsx1TrapPortId
dlcDsx1TrapPortId.description: Uniquely identifies this port. Valid values are `mainNet', `aux', `otherNet'.

dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap.name: dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap
dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap.description: Defines Bipolar Violation Error Rate threshold in units of BPV errors per minute. When this threshold is exceeded, the unit will send a trap to the SNMP manager. The threshold is of the form M x 10 ^ -E where M is a mantissa and E the exponent. Both are single digit values. M and E are represented in this value as one number: (M) x 10 + (E). For example, the threshold 7x10^-3 BPVs/min is encoded as the integer 73. A value of 0 disables the trap altogether. Valid values for dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap are: 13 23 33 43 53 63 14 24 34 44 54 64 74 84 94 15 25 35 45 55 65 75 85 95 16 26 36 46 56 66 76 86 96 17 27 37 47 57 67 77 87 97 28 38 48 58 68 78 88 98 or, from 6E-3 to 2E-8. N.B. The BPV Threshold Alarm exists only for the mainNet and otherNet Port IDs, so setting the Threshold for the aux PortId will always fail. The BPV Threshold is always reported as 0 for the aux PortId.

dlcDsx1OofThresholdTrap.name: dlcDsx1OofThresholdTrap
dlcDsx1OofThresholdTrap.description: Defines the Out Of Frame Error Rate threshold in units of OOF errors per minute. The threshold is encoded the same as dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap. A value of 0 disables the trap altogether. Valid values for dlcDsx1OofThresholdTap are: 12 22 22 42 52 62 72 13 23 33 43 53 63 73 83 93 14 24 34 44 54 64 74 84 94 15 25 35 45 55 65 75 85 95 36 46 56 66 76 86 96 or, from 7E-2 to 3E-6. N.B. The OOF Threshold Alarm exists only for the mainNet and otherNet Port IDs, so setting the Threshold for the aux PortId will always fail. The OOF Threshold is always reported as 0 for the aux PortId.

dlcDsx1CrcThresholdTrap.name: dlcDsx1CrcThresholdTrap
dlcDsx1CrcThresholdTrap.description: Defines the CRC-6 Error Rate threshold in units of CRC errors per minute. The threshold is encoded the same as dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap. A value of 0 disables the trap altogether. Valid values for dlcDsx1CrcThresholdTrap are: 10 11 21 31 41 51 61 71 81 91 12 22 32 42 52 62 72 82 92 13 23 33 43 53 63 73 83 93 14 24 34 44 54 64 74 84 94 55 65 75 85 95 or, from 1E0 to 5E-5. N.B. The CRC Threshold Alarm exists only for the mainNet and otherNet Port IDs, so setting the Threshold for the aux PortId will always fail. The CRC Threshold is always reported as 0 for the aux PortId.

dlcDsx1LossOfSignalTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1LossOfSignalTrapEnable
dlcDsx1LossOfSignalTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon loss of network signal (LOS) on a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1LossOfSyncTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1LossOfSyncTrapEnable
dlcDsx1LossOfSyncTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon loss of network framing (LOF) on a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1ReceiveAIStrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1ReceiveAIStrapEnable
dlcDsx1ReceiveAIStrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of AIS (Blue Alarm Signal) on a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1ReceiveYellowAlarmTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1ReceiveYellowAlarmTrapEnable
dlcDsx1ReceiveYellowAlarmTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of Yellow Alarm Signal on a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1ReceiveRemoteAlarmTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1ReceiveRemoteAlarmTrapEnable
dlcDsx1ReceiveRemoteAlarmTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of Remote Alarm Indicator on an E1 Dsx1 port. For T1 units, this object's value will always be read as 0 and set operations will succeed, but the value will not be changed.

dlcDsx1PSfailureTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1PSfailureTrapEnable
dlcDsx1PSfailureTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon a power supply failure. This object doesn't really belong in the dlcDsx1TrapEnableTable. It is specific to units that are installed in a shelf. When accessing this object, the index (portId) is ignored.

dlcDsx1CntlCrdMissingTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1CntlCrdMissingTrapEnable
dlcDsx1CntlCrdMissingTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of a missing controller card. This object doesn't really belong in the dlcDsx1TrapEnableTable. It is specific to units that are installed in a shelf. When accessing this object, the index (portId) is ignored.

dlcDsx1FdlLinkTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1FdlLinkTrapEnable
dlcDsx1FdlLinkTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of the remote unit is not responding to DLC FDL messages.

dlcDsx1IbCrcThresholdTrap.name: dlcDsx1IbCrcThresholdTrap
dlcDsx1IbCrcThresholdTrap.description: Defines the In-Band CRC Error Rate threshold in units of CRC errors per minute. The threshold is encoded the same as dlcDsx1BpvThresholdTrap. A value of 0 disables the trap altogether. For the Eclipse, valid values of dlcDsx1IbCrcThresholdTrap range from 47 to 91. N.B. The CRC Threshold Alarm exists only for the mainNet port.

dlcDsx1InbandLinkTrapEnable.name: dlcDsx1InbandLinkTrapEnable
dlcDsx1InbandLinkTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of the inband link.

dlcUnitDataDteLossTrapEnableTable.name: dlcUnitDataDteLossTrapEnableTable
dlcUnitDataDteLossTrapEnableTable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon the loss of signal on a Data DTE port.

dlcDataDteLossTrapEnableEntry.name: dlcDataDteLossTrapEnableEntry
dlcDataDteLossTrapEnableEntry.description: An entry in the Data DTE Loss Trap Enable table.

dlcDataLossPortId.name: dlcDataLossPortId
dlcDataLossPortId.description: Uniquely identifies this port. Valid values are `data1' through `data32'.

dlcDataLossEnable.name: dlcDataLossEnable
dlcDataLossEnable.description: Says whether to enable this trap.

dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputTrapEnable.name: dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputTrapEnable
dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables a trap upon detection of an alarm condition on the External Alarm Input.

dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputContacts.name: dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputContacts
dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputContacts.description: When set to normallyOpen, an alarm is declared when the contacts close ... and vice-versa.

dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputMessage.name: dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputMessage
dlcUnitExternalAlarmInputMessage.description: A character string that describes what's going on when an alarm on the External Alarm Input is detected.

dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputContacts.name: dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputContacts
dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputContacts.description: When set to normallyOpen, the contacts close when any enabled alarm occurs and vice-versa. Pushing any button on the units Front Panel will cause the alarm contacts to open again until another alarm is recognized.

dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputTrapEnable.name: dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputTrapEnable
dlcUnitExternalAlarmOutputTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables the external alarm output contacts.

dlcUnitDsx1ConfigTable.name: dlcUnitDsx1ConfigTable
dlcUnitDsx1ConfigTable.description: A table of configuration items for a Dsx1 port.

dlcDsx1ConfigEntry.name: dlcDsx1ConfigEntry
dlcDsx1ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Dsx1 configuration table.

dlcDsx1ConfigPortId.name: dlcDsx1ConfigPortId
dlcDsx1ConfigPortId.description: Uniquely identifies this port. Valid values are `mainNet', `aux', `otherNet'.

dlcDsx1Framing.name: dlcDsx1Framing
dlcDsx1Framing.description: Dsx1 framing type: T1 --> D4 or ESF; E1 --> CRC4 or not. Unstructured is E1 only, when in this mode, the E1 line acts like a 2048 Bps pipe with no framing information.

dlcDsx1LineCode.name: dlcDsx1LineCode
dlcDsx1LineCode.description: Dsx1 line code type, AMI or B8ZS. E1 lines are always HDB3.

dlcDsx1LineMatching.name: dlcDsx1LineMatching
dlcDsx1LineMatching.description: Dsx1 line build out or equalization: For a T1 NET port, LBO is 0, -7.5 or -15dB. For a T1 AUX port, EQ is 0..533 feet. For any E1 port, impedance is 75 or 120 Ohms.

dlcDsx1DacsMode.name: dlcDsx1DacsMode
dlcDsx1DacsMode.description: True if DACS mode is in effect for this port.

dlcDsx1UseDlcFdlProtocol.name: dlcDsx1UseDlcFdlProtocol
dlcDsx1UseDlcFdlProtocol.description: True when DLC FDL protocol is enabled over this port's FDL.

dlcDsx1UseAnsiProtocol.name: dlcDsx1UseAnsiProtocol
dlcDsx1UseAnsiProtocol.description: True if ANSI Dsx1.403 is enabled over the FDL.

dlcDsx1Bit7Stuffing.name: dlcDsx1Bit7Stuffing
dlcDsx1Bit7Stuffing.description: When true, bit 7 stuffing is turned on for a T1 Aux port to provide pulse density protection. Valid only on a T1 AUX port.

dlcDsx1InBandBit.name: dlcDsx1InBandBit
dlcDsx1InBandBit.description: Specifies which bit in Timeslot 1 of an E1 link is used to pass message traffic. Not implemented for T1 ports.

dlcDataDteConfigEntry.name: dlcDataDteConfigEntry
dlcDataDteConfigEntry.description: An entry in the data DTE configuration table.

dlcDataConfigPortId.name: dlcDataConfigPortId
dlcDataConfigPortId.description: Uniquely identifies this port. Valid values are `data1' through `data32'.

dlcDataConfigLoss.name: dlcDataConfigLoss
dlcDataConfigLoss.description: The criterion to declare a Loss of Data DTE.

dlcDataConfigMode.name: dlcDataConfigMode
dlcDataConfigMode.description: In dteMode the unit is the DTE and the external equipment the DCE.

dlcDataConfigTransmitTiming.name: dlcDataConfigTransmitTiming
dlcDataConfigTransmitTiming.description: Selects the Data DTE tramsmit timing source. Can be SCTE, SCT or inverted SCT.

dlcUnitMuxConfigTable.name: dlcUnitMuxConfigTable
dlcUnitMuxConfigTable.description: This is the timeslot map configuration.

dlcMuxConfigEntry.name: dlcMuxConfigEntry
dlcMuxConfigEntry.description: An entry in the timeslot map.

dlcMuxConfigBusId.name: dlcMuxConfigBusId
dlcMuxConfigBusId.description: Identifies which muxBus this timeslot is on.

dlcMuxConfigPortId.name: dlcMuxConfigPortId
dlcMuxConfigPortId.description: Says which DTE port receives data from the indicated muxBus during this timeslot.

dlcSnmpUnitIpAddr.name: dlcSnmpUnitIpAddr
dlcSnmpUnitIpAddr.description: Specifies the IP address that is assigned to this unit.

dlcSnmpUnitNetMask.name: dlcSnmpUnitNetMask
dlcSnmpUnitNetMask.description: Specifies the net mask that this unit uses.

dlcSnmpTrapAddr1.name: dlcSnmpTrapAddr1
dlcSnmpTrapAddr1.description: Specifies the IP address of the management station to which this unit sends traps.

dlcSnmpTrapAddr2.name: dlcSnmpTrapAddr2
dlcSnmpTrapAddr2.description: Specifies the IP address of the management station to which this unit sends traps.

dlcSnmpTrapAddr3.name: dlcSnmpTrapAddr3
dlcSnmpTrapAddr3.description: Specifies the IP address of the management station to which this unit sends traps.

dlcSnmpTrapDlci1.name: dlcSnmpTrapDlci1
dlcSnmpTrapDlci1.description: Specifies the first of three DLCI value to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDlci2.name: dlcSnmpTrapDlci2
dlcSnmpTrapDlci2.description: Specifies the second of three DLCI value to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDlci3.name: dlcSnmpTrapDlci3
dlcSnmpTrapDlci3.description: Specifies the third of three DLCI value to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDirection1.name: dlcSnmpTrapDirection1
dlcSnmpTrapDirection1.description: Specifies the first of three Port to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDirection2.name: dlcSnmpTrapDirection2
dlcSnmpTrapDirection2.description: Specifies the second of three Port to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDirection3.name: dlcSnmpTrapDirection3
dlcSnmpTrapDirection3.description: Specifies the third of three Port to which this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcSnmpTrapDirection.name: dlcSnmpTrapDirection
dlcSnmpTrapDirection.description: Specifies where this unit sends TRAP PDUs.

dlcEthernetIpAddr.name: dlcEthernetIpAddr
dlcEthernetIpAddr.description: Specifies the IP address of Ethernet port.

dlcEthernetIpMask.name: dlcEthernetIpMask
dlcEthernetIpMask.description: Specifies the subnet mask of Ethernet port.

dlcEthernetGatewayAddr.name: dlcEthernetGatewayAddr
dlcEthernetGatewayAddr.description: Specifies the gateway address of Ethernet port.

dlcEthernetMacAddr.name: dlcEthernetMacAddr
dlcEthernetMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the Ethernet port.

dlcUnitTimeYear.name: dlcUnitTimeYear
dlcUnitTimeYear.description: The unit's notion of the current year.

dlcUnitTimeMonth.name: dlcUnitTimeMonth
dlcUnitTimeMonth.description: The unit's notion of the current month.

dlcUnitTimeDay.name: dlcUnitTimeDay
dlcUnitTimeDay.description: The unit's notion of the current day.

dlcUnitTimeHour.name: dlcUnitTimeHour
dlcUnitTimeHour.description: The the unit's notion of the current hour.

dlcUnitTimeMinute.name: dlcUnitTimeMinute
dlcUnitTimeMinute.description: The the unit's notion of the current minute.

dlcUnitTimeSecond.name: dlcUnitTimeSecond
dlcUnitTimeSecond.description: The the unit's notion of the current second.

dlcUnitSerialNum.name: dlcUnitSerialNum
dlcUnitSerialNum.description: An ID that uniquely and globally identifies the unit. A Serial Number must consist of printable ASCII characters 0x20 ..0x7E.

dlcModemPhoneNum1.name: dlcModemPhoneNum1
dlcModemPhoneNum1.description: The first phone number to dial when the unit needs to set up a modem connection.

dlcModemPhoneNum2.name: dlcModemPhoneNum2
dlcModemPhoneNum2.description: The second phone number to try if the phone number failed in setting up a modem connection.

dlcModemInitString1.name: dlcModemInitString1
dlcModemInitString1.description: In setting up a modem connection, the first group of commands used to initialize the modem.

dlcModemInitString2.name: dlcModemInitString2
dlcModemInitString2.description: In setting up a modem connection, the second group of commands used to initialize the modem. There is a delay between sending the first and second groups of initialzation commands.

dlcUnitInbandMode.name: dlcUnitInbandMode
dlcUnitInbandMode.description: The type of traffic expected on the link for inband management and IPM.

dlcUnitCurrentStatus.name: dlcUnitCurrentStatus
dlcUnitCurrentStatus.description: What's going on in this unit?

dlcUnitErrorFreeSeconds.name: dlcUnitErrorFreeSeconds
dlcUnitErrorFreeSeconds.description: Represents the percent of error free seconds over the last 24 hours. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcUnitLastSelfTestResult.name: dlcUnitLastSelfTestResult
dlcUnitLastSelfTestResult.description: The result of the last self test. unitLastSelfTest is a bitmap ... the sum of: 0 Selftest passed 1 ROM checksum failure 2 RAM test failure 4 EEPROM CRC failure 8 DTE test failure 16 Pattern loss during test 32 FLASH checksum failure 64 reserved 128 reserved 256 reserved 512 reserved A result of 0 means no errors occurred.

dlcUnitPortStatusTable.name: dlcUnitPortStatusTable
dlcUnitPortStatusTable.description: A table of all port-related status

dlcPortStatusEntry.name: dlcPortStatusEntry
dlcPortStatusEntry.description: An entry in the port status table.

dlcPortStatusId.name: dlcPortStatusId
dlcPortStatusId.description: Identifies which port (NET, AUX, Data DTE, or whatever) this status entry is describing.

dlcPortStatus.name: dlcPortStatus
dlcPortStatus.description: Gives the actual status value for to this port.

dlcPortStatusNetRxBwUtilization.name: dlcPortStatusNetRxBwUtilization
dlcPortStatusNetRxBwUtilization.description: Represents the percent of net receive bandwidth utilization over the last 60 seconds. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcPortStatusNetTxBwUtilization.name: dlcPortStatusNetTxBwUtilization
dlcPortStatusNetTxBwUtilization.description: Represents the percent of net receive bandwidth utilization over the last 60 seconds. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcUnitAlarmTable.name: dlcUnitAlarmTable
dlcUnitAlarmTable.description: A table of all currently-raised alarms

dlcAlarmEntry.name: dlcAlarmEntry
dlcAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the alarm table.

dlcAlarmPort.name: dlcAlarmPort
dlcAlarmPort.description: Identifies which port (NET, AUX, Data DTE, or whatever) this alarm relates to.

dlcAlarmType.name: dlcAlarmType
dlcAlarmType.description: Identifies an alarm that's currently outstanding against this port.

dlcUnitErrorSecondsRatio.name: dlcUnitErrorSecondsRatio
dlcUnitErrorSecondsRatio.description: Represents the percent of error seconds over the last 24 hours. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcUnitSeverelyErroredSecondsRatio.name: dlcUnitSeverelyErroredSecondsRatio
dlcUnitSeverelyErroredSecondsRatio.description: Represents the percent of severely errored seconds over the last 24 hours. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcUnitBackgroundBlockErrorRatio.name: dlcUnitBackgroundBlockErrorRatio
dlcUnitBackgroundBlockErrorRatio.description: Represents the percent of background block errors over the last 24 hours. The number is multiplied by 10 and rounded to the nearest integer. For example, 94.2% is encoded as 942.

dlcUnitUserArchiveValidTable.name: dlcUnitUserArchiveValidTable
dlcUnitUserArchiveValidTable.description: A table of all port-related status

dlcUserArchiveValidEntry.name: dlcUserArchiveValidEntry
dlcUserArchiveValidEntry.description: An entry in the user archive valid-intervals table.

dlcValidPortId.name: dlcValidPortId
dlcValidPortId.description: Identifies which port (`net' or `otherNet') this entry is describing.

dlcValidIntervals.name: dlcValidIntervals
dlcValidIntervals.description: The number of valid intervals in the user's error register database for this port. Writing a 0 to this variable will clear the entire archive for this port. Writing any other value is a no-op.

dlcUnitUserLifetimeTable.name: dlcUnitUserLifetimeTable
dlcUnitUserLifetimeTable.description: A table of the lifetime error counts, per-port.

dlcUserLifetimeEntry.name: dlcUserLifetimeEntry
dlcUserLifetimeEntry.description: An entry in the user archive lifetime-totals table.

dlcLifetimePortId.name: dlcLifetimePortId
dlcLifetimePortId.description: Identifies which port (`net' or `otherNet') this entry relates to.

dlcLifetimeES.name: dlcLifetimeES
dlcLifetimeES.description: An ongoing count of Errored Seconds detected on this network port. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLifetimeUAS.name: dlcLifetimeUAS
dlcLifetimeUAS.description: An ongoing count of Unavailable Seconds detected on this network port. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLifetimeCrcErrors.name: dlcLifetimeCrcErrors
dlcLifetimeCrcErrors.description: An ongoing count of the CRC errors detected on this network port. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLifetimeBpvErrors.name: dlcLifetimeBpvErrors
dlcLifetimeBpvErrors.description: An ongoing count of the Code Violation errors detected on this network port. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLifetimeOofErrors.name: dlcLifetimeOofErrors
dlcLifetimeOofErrors.description: For an ESF T1 port, an ongoing count of Out-Of-Frame errors. For a D4 T1 port, an ongoing count of Framing Errors. Available only for the network port. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLifetimeIbCrcErrors.name: dlcLifetimeIbCrcErrors
dlcLifetimeIbCrcErrors.description: An ongoing count of the FCS errors detected on this network port.

dlcUnitUserCurrentTable.name: dlcUnitUserCurrentTable
dlcUnitUserCurrentTable.description: A table of all the current interval error counts, per-port.

dlcUserCurrentEntry.name: dlcUserCurrentEntry
dlcUserCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the user archive current interval table.

dlcCurrentPortId.name: dlcCurrentPortId
dlcCurrentPortId.description: Identifies which port (`net' or `otherNet') this entry relates to.

dlcCurrentBpvErrors.name: dlcCurrentBpvErrors
dlcCurrentBpvErrors.description: Code Violation Errors in the interval.

dlcCurrentOofErrors.name: dlcCurrentOofErrors
dlcCurrentOofErrors.description: OOF or Framing Errors in the interval.

dlcCurrentTimeElapsed.name: dlcCurrentTimeElapsed
dlcCurrentTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement period. Available only for the network port.

dlcUnitUserArchiveTable.name: dlcUnitUserArchiveTable
dlcUnitUserArchiveTable.description: A table of all the archive intervals' error counts, per-port.

dlcUserArchiveEntry.name: dlcUserArchiveEntry
dlcUserArchiveEntry.description: An entry in the user archive table.

dlcArchivePortId.name: dlcArchivePortId
dlcArchivePortId.description: Identifies which port (`net' or `otherNet') this entry relates to.

dlcArchiveInterval.name: dlcArchiveInterval
dlcArchiveInterval.description: Identifies which interval this secondaryArchiveEntry describes. 1 indicates the most-recent interval.

dlcArchiveBpvErrors.name: dlcArchiveBpvErrors
dlcArchiveBpvErrors.description: Code Violation Errors in the interval.

dlcArchiveOofErrors.name: dlcArchiveOofErrors
dlcArchiveOofErrors.description: OOF or Framing Errors in the interval.

dlcArchiveNetRxBwUtilization.name: dlcArchiveNetRxBwUtilization
dlcArchiveNetRxBwUtilization.description: Net Rx Bandwidth Utilization in the interval.

dlcArchiveNetRxPackets.name: dlcArchiveNetRxPackets
dlcArchiveNetRxPackets.description: Net Rx Packets in the interval.

dlcArchiveNetTxBwUtilization.name: dlcArchiveNetTxBwUtilization
dlcArchiveNetTxBwUtilization.description: Net Tx Bandwidth Utilization in the interval.

dlcUnitTestTable.name: dlcUnitTestTable
dlcUnitTestTable.description: A table containing all currently active tests. The initial release of the product's firmware does not include multiple tests. However, a later version will allow a number of tests to be active at a time. This MIB object structure allows any number of tests to be running at any time. Upon receiving a SET request, the unit compares this table with the list of currently active tests and terminates or initiates any tests as required. However, this does not apply to Link Based Test. dlcUnitConfigLinkTest group contains objects to configure and start Link Based Test. This table only contains the statistics for Link Based Test.

dlcUnitTestEntry.name: dlcUnitTestEntry
dlcUnitTestEntry.description: An entry in the network configuration table.

dlcUnitTestPortId.name: dlcUnitTestPortId
dlcUnitTestPortId.description: Identifies a port that a test might be running on. By convention, Self Test and all full-bandwidth tests (loopbacks, patterns, etc.) are assigned to the netPort. For E1 unit, if it is in unstructured mode, only full-bandwidth tests can be performed.

dlcUnitTestType.name: dlcUnitTestType
dlcUnitTestType.description: Says what test is running on this port. Note that the following test nomenclature is equivalent: SNMP Terminal UI Front Panel 1in8 1:7 1:7 3in24 3:24 3.24 1in1 1:1 1:1 AllOne All 1 1's AllZero All 0 0's 1in3 1:2 1:2 1in5 1:4 1:4 The SNMP test identifiers use the names on the left. The terminal User Interface uses the names in the middle column, and the unit's front panel uses the names in the right column.

dlcUnitTestPatternStatus.name: dlcUnitTestPatternStatus
dlcUnitTestPatternStatus.description: The current state of the Pattern Test module.

dlcUnitTestPatternErrors.name: dlcUnitTestPatternErrors
dlcUnitTestPatternErrors.description: An ongoing count of errors detected by the Pattern Generator/Detector. Can be read and written (to zero).

dlcLinkTestSentPackets.name: dlcLinkTestSentPackets
dlcLinkTestSentPackets.description: Number of sent packets for the currently running link based test.

dlcLinkTestReceivedPackets.name: dlcLinkTestReceivedPackets

dlcLinkTestErroredPackets.name: dlcLinkTestErroredPackets
dlcLinkTestErroredPackets.description: Number of errored received packets for the currently running link based test.

dlcLinkTestMissingPackets.name: dlcLinkTestMissingPackets
dlcLinkTestMissingPackets.description: Number of missing packets for the currently running link based test.

dlcLinkTestAverageRoundTrip.name: dlcLinkTestAverageRoundTrip
dlcLinkTestAverageRoundTrip.description: Average round trip time in milli seconds for the currently running link based test.

dlcLinkTestMaximumRoundTrip.name: dlcLinkTestMaximumRoundTrip
dlcLinkTestMaximumRoundTrip.description: Maximum round trip time in milli seconds for the currently running link based test.

dlcUnitDialOutTimeInterval.name: dlcUnitDialOutTimeInterval
dlcUnitDialOutTimeInterval.description: A time interval for the dialout. The value should be between 0 and 255.

dlcUnitIdleCode.name: dlcUnitIdleCode
dlcUnitIdleCode.description: Idle Code that is send on unassigned time slots

dlcLinkTestState.name: dlcLinkTestState
dlcLinkTestState.description: Specifies the status configuration of link based test. Only setable to values disabled(1) and enabled(2) to end and start the test respectively. Values running(3) and idle(4) are returned for status of the test.

dlcLinkTestAddress.name: dlcLinkTestAddress
dlcLinkTestAddress.description: Specifies the address for the next link based test to run.

dlcLinkTestDlci.name: dlcLinkTestDlci
dlcLinkTestDlci.description: Specifies the frame relay DLCI for the next link based test to run. This value is used when the unit is in frameRelay InbandMode only and if the next link based test is not done on the commPort.

dlcLinkTestPort.name: dlcLinkTestPort
dlcLinkTestPort.description: Specifies which port to run the next link based test.

dlcLinkTestLength.name: dlcLinkTestLength
dlcLinkTestLength.description: Specifies the time length of the next test to run in minutes.

dlcLinkTestInterval.name: dlcLinkTestInterval
dlcLinkTestInterval.description: Specifies the repetition interval in seconds between packets for the next link based test.

dlcLinkTestPacketSize.name: dlcLinkTestPacketSize
dlcLinkTestPacketSize.description: Specifies the packet size for the next link based test.

dlcLinkTestPattern.name: dlcLinkTestPattern
dlcLinkTestPattern.description: Specifies the test pattern for the next link based test.

dlcUnitInbandConfig.name: dlcUnitInbandConfig
dlcUnitInbandConfig.description: When true (== 2), inband management is enabled.

dlcUnitInbandTrafficType.name: dlcUnitInbandTrafficType
dlcUnitInbandTrafficType.description: The type of traffic expected on the link for inband management and IPM.

dlcUnitPerformanceMonitoring.name: dlcUnitPerformanceMonitoring
dlcUnitPerformanceMonitoring.description: When true (== 2), the integrated performance monitoring (IPM) is enabled

dlcUnitPvcAutoDiscovery.name: dlcUnitPvcAutoDiscovery
dlcUnitPvcAutoDiscovery.description: When true (== 2), automatic discovery of DLCIs is enabled

dlcDelayMonitorConfigIndex.description: Uniquely identifies which delay monitor test in the configuration table.

dlcDelayMonitorState.name: dlcDelayMonitorState
dlcDelayMonitorState.description: Specifies the status configuration of this delay monitor. Only setable to values disabled(1) and enabled(2) to end and start the test respectively. Values running(3) and idle(4) are returned for status of the test.

dlcDelayMonitorDlci.description: Specifies the frame relay DLCI for the next delay monitor to run. This value is used when the unit is in frameRelay InbandMode only and if the next delay monitor is not done on the commPort.

dlcDelayMonitorMaximumRoundTrip.description: Maximum round trip time in milli seconds for the currently running delay monitor test.

dlcDTECIR.description: This DLCI's DTE Confirmed Information Rate (CIR)

dlcNETCIR.description: This DLCI's NET Confirmed Information Rate (CIR)

dlcDLCIstatus.name: dlcDLCIstatus
dlcDLCIstatus.description: This object represents status of the entry. When read, it will return status 'active' or 'inactive' representing the status of the row. When written, this object is used to add or delete entry. Setting to 'enabled' will add a new entry, setting to 'disabled' will delete the entry.

dlcUtilTableEntry.name: dlcUtilTableEntry
dlcUtilTableEntry.description: An entry for the utilization table.

dlcUtilDLCINumber.name: dlcUtilDLCINumber
dlcUtilDLCINumber.description: Identifies the DLCI number of the utilization statistics of this entry/row.

dlcUtilEncodedValue.name: dlcUtilEncodedValue
dlcUtilEncodedValue.description: This object represents the value of the whole row of the table. The intent of object is to increase the efficiency of retrieving the table. For each object value in this table, which are all of Counter type, it will be represented with 4 bytes of data.

dlcUtilTimestamp.name: dlcUtilTimestamp
dlcUtilTimestamp.description: Identifies timestamp when this entry is last updated.

dlcUtilLessThan20.name: dlcUtilLessThan20
dlcUtilLessThan20.description: The number of times utilization is less than 20% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcUtil20_40.name: dlcUtil20_40
dlcUtil20_40.description: The number of times utilization is between 20% and 40% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcUtil40_60.name: dlcUtil40_60
dlcUtil40_60.description: The number of times utilization is between 40% and 60% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcUtil60_80.name: dlcUtil60_80
dlcUtil60_80.description: The number of times utilization is between 60% and 80% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcUtil80_100.name: dlcUtil80_100
dlcUtil80_100.description: The number of times utilization is between 80% and 100% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcUtilMoreThan100.name: dlcUtilMoreThan100
dlcUtilMoreThan100.description: The number of times utilization is more than 100% of Committed Information Rate (CIR).

dlcLMIEnable.name: dlcLMIEnable
dlcLMIEnable.description: This object specifies whether to enable or disable LMI Conditioning.

dlcMaintenanceDLCI.name: dlcMaintenanceDLCI
dlcMaintenanceDLCI.description: This objects specifies the status of the LMI Spoofing.

dlcManagementDLCI.name: dlcManagementDLCI
dlcManagementDLCI.description: This objects specifies the number of management DLCI between 16 and 991 inclusive. Must not be the same as maintenance DLCI. Default is 989.

dlcManagementDLCIEnable.name: dlcManagementDLCIEnable
dlcManagementDLCIEnable.description: This object specifies whether to enable or disable Management DLCI.

dlcSpoofingProtocolType.name: dlcSpoofingProtocolType
dlcSpoofingProtocolType.description: This objects configures which LMI message type to 'spoof', in the event that spoofing is activated. The possible choices are FRF 1.0 (Frame Relay Forum's early LMI adaptation), Annex A (ITU Q.933, annex A), and Annex D (ANSI T1.617, annex D). Default is Annex D.

dlcDTESpoofingEnable.name: dlcDTESpoofingEnable
dlcDTESpoofingEnable.description: If the value of this object is 'enabled', LMI spoofing to the DTE port is done automatically.

dlcNetSpoofingEnable.name: dlcNetSpoofingEnable
dlcNetSpoofingEnable.description: If the value of this object is 'enabled', LMI spoofing to the Network port is done automatically.

dlcLinkIntegrityVerificationPollingTimer.name: dlcLinkIntegrityVerificationPollingTimer
dlcLinkIntegrityVerificationPollingTimer.description: This object is the interval in seconds between Link Integrity Verification Messages. This is known as T391 in the standards. Possible values are 5 to 30 seconds in increments of 5. Default is 10 seconds.

dlcFullStatusPollingCounter.name: dlcFullStatusPollingCounter
dlcFullStatusPollingCounter.description: This value corresponds to N391 in the ITU and ANSI standards. It is the number of polling cycles of the type before the unit generates the full status request. Possible values are 1 to 255. Default is 10.

dlcLMIErrorEvent.name: dlcLMIErrorEvent
dlcLMIErrorEvent.description: This object configures the parameter which sets the number of errors that can occur on the LMI link in LMI Error Monitored Events before reporting an interface down. Applies to the DTE and Network ports. This is used in the same manner as the N392 parameter (N2) in the standards. Possible values are 1 to 10. Default is 1.

dlcLMIErrorMonitorEvent.name: dlcLMIErrorMonitorEvent
dlcLMIErrorMonitorEvent.description: This object configures parameter which sets the number of events that are used with the LMI Error Event to define the error ratio that is used to report when the LMI link is down. Applies to the DTE and Network ports. This value is used in the same manner as the N393 parameter (N3) in the standards.

dlcLMIErrorFreeEvent.name: dlcLMIErrorFreeEvent
dlcLMIErrorFreeEvent.description: This object configures the parameter which sets the number of error-free messages that must be received in LMI Error Free Monitored Events prior to declaring an interface is up. Applies to the DTE and Network ports. For network spoofing, this is the number of error-free events that will cause the DSU to believe the network is back up and runnig, and the DSU will stop spoofing. This is used in the same manner as the N392 parameter (N2) in the standards. Possible values are 1 to 10. Default is 1.

dlcLMIErrorFreeMonitorEvent.name: dlcLMIErrorFreeMonitorEvent
dlcLMIErrorFreeMonitorEvent.description: This object configures parameter which sets the number of events that are used with the LMI Error Free Event to define the error ratio that is used to report that the LMI link is up. Applies to the DTE and Network ports. This is used in the same manner as the N393 parameter (N3) in the standards.

dlcDTEResponseTimer.name: dlcDTEResponseTimer
dlcDTEResponseTimer.description: This object configures the parameter which sets the number of seconds between the sending of a status enquiry message and the receipt of a response. Applies to the DTE port. This value is similar in nature to the T392 (T2) parameter in the standards. Possible values are 5 to 30 in increments of 5. Default is 15.

dlcLMIUnitLocation.name: dlcLMIUnitLocation
dlcLMIUnitLocation.description: This object configures where the unit is located so that LMI spoofing could be done properly. If 'cpe' is selected, it means the unit is located in Customer Premise. If 'co' is selected, the unit is in Central Office.

dlcSpoofingStatus.name: dlcSpoofingStatus
dlcSpoofingStatus.description: This object configures automatic LMI spoofing to the router. 'True' means LMI spoofing will occur automatically, 'False' means it's disabled.

dlcDTEInterfaceLMIStatus.name: dlcDTEInterfaceLMIStatus
dlcDTEInterfaceLMIStatus.description: This object indicates the LMI status of DTE interface.

dlcNetInterfaceLMIStatus.name: dlcNetInterfaceLMIStatus
dlcNetInterfaceLMIStatus.description: This object indicates the LMI status of Net interface.

dlcInbandDtePort.name: dlcInbandDtePort
dlcInbandDtePort.description: This object configures which DTE port has inband management.

startTest.description: Sent upon the initiation of a new test condition.

endTest.name: endTest
endTest.description: Sent upon the termination of a test condition.

startAlarm.description: Indicates the beginning of a new alarm condition.

endAlarm.name: endAlarm
endAlarm.description: Indicates the end of an alarm condition.
